. if you're even in ornate gear, your pet will take substantially more DDPS than you, I.E. you are mostly better off tanking while you heal yourself.<br><br>It's really kind of annoying me.  Beastlords are supposed to be dps.  Completely eliminating the recast timer would not be overpowering, *at all.*  Where I am now, I could chain the nukes an entire boss-mob length fight without running oom if needed, if there was no recast... but where I am now, chain casting that nuke would be half the dps of a rogue.  <br><br>at levels where the dps from chaining that nuke would be overpowering, a beastlord will not have the manapool/UMR to chain it.<br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 31 00:42:11 2005 by czaemon</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.czaemon.com" target="akztarg">Czaemon</a><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1187570" target="akztarg">Tehlar</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from I'M IN UR BASE, KILLING UR DOODZ!</td></tr></table>
